begin_memory_text: We talked about where we each live. He described the small town area he lives in relative to distance to hospitals. We talked about the work we do.
middle_memory_text: We talked about Covid and how it's affecting work and life. We talked about his wife's work at the Health Department. He told a story about stopping at a gas station during the early days of masking.
end_memory_text: We were talking about home repairs he was working on, trouble getting furniture from Lazyboy, and I talked about my parents' home renovations.
rest_of_day_open: I think it will be a slog. I overdid it yesterday and am a bit low on energy and not feeling very well today. But I am doing a lot of laundry today and some cooking. Tomorrow, I need to work on Christmas planning and some clean up and clean out chores around the house.
critical_positive: I feel like we have a strong similarity in being people whose hearts lie in the small town life. That gave me a sense that this was a person similar to me in worldview. It was also helpful that we both started out in a similar career field so that gave us some early things to talk about and had the shared experience of the recent selling of a family home.
critical_negative: During the first half, I thought we both seemed somewhat distracted and unengaged from the conversation. My conversation partner seemed to maybe have a hard time coming up with topics to talk about. This is likely because this is his first conversation and he wasn't quite sure yet how it usually goes.

begin_memory_text: We talked about where we were from and where we live. I told her about being in the middle of nowhere in Ohio and she told me about living outside of Chicago. We discussed her having family from Ohio and they actually were from a town near where my family owned a farm and had lived in the past.
middle_memory_text: We talked about careers. At one point I mentioned that I was hired to be a librarian and she told me she had the same degree I did, which was very interesting. She also told me about her husband since he was in school when she left her library job, then he became a lawyer.
end_memory_text: We talked about the coronavirus and the lockdowns, as well as parenting children in small towns. She told me about how sometimes her husband explained that people get charged with ridiculous things, but he is a public defender. We discussed things like underage driving -- as a child I drove into town from the farm on a go-cart, for example -- and how everyone knowing everyone in a town is generally a good thing for families.
rest_of_day_open: I think it will be a lot of fun. I'm off work tomorrow and will spend the day doing some activities I really enjoy. I have the chance to watch my son play ball this evening as long as it doesn't rain, so that's enjoyable. And I have the weekend with just my wife, which is something I always look forward to.
critical_positive: I think it worked out well that we had similar education backgrounds but different educational experiences. I think that it also worked out well that she knew how this would go a little bit since it was my first time trying to complete one of these. It was helpful to be having a conversation with someone that knew what we were doing.
critical_negative: I don't think anything didn't work out well specifically. I often worry that I'm talking too much and not letting the other person participate in the story of a conversation. I tried to be aware of that, but maybe I was still a bit overbearing in this conversation. I think the partner I had was great and didn't seem too annoyed by it though.
